# Validation workflow

**MANDATORY:** A task is not complete until `/dev-validate` passes — see [commands/validate.md](../commands/validate.md).

## Auto-fix loop (max 6 iterations)

1. Run `/dev-validate` (or `/dev-validate --quick` mid-task) — agent executes `tsx skills/scripts/validate.ts`
2. Parse failures by category: typecheck | lint | tenant | zod | tests
3. Fix highest-priority category first
4. Re-run validation
5. Repeat until clean or iteration 6

## Priority order

| Priority | Category | Command |
|----------|----------|---------|
| P0 | Tenant scope P0 | `npm run audit:tenant-scope:p0` |
| P1 | TypeScript | `npm run typecheck` |
| P2 | Mutating Zod | `npm run audit:mutating-zod` |
| P3 | Lint (touched files) | `npm run lint` |
| P4 | Unit tests | `npm run test:ci` |
| P5 | Smoke E2E | `npm run test:e2e:smoke` |

## After intentional deviation

`/dev-learn capture --suggested "..." --actual "..." --reason "..."`

Or:

`/dev-learn auto --staged`

## Never claim complete when

- Typecheck has errors
- `audit:tenant-scope:p0` fails on touched APIs
- New mutating route lacks Zod
- Migration not applied on clean DB (if schema changed)
